{"title_page": "TheOdd1sOut", "text_new": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American YouTuber}}{{BLP sources|date=November 2019}}{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{humour}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name= TheOdd1sOut \n| image = James_Rallison_at_Vidcon.jpg\n| caption = Rallison at [[VidCon]] 2017, wearing a shirt featuring his YouTube persona\n| birth_name = Robert James Rallison\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|5|14}}<ref>{{cite web|title=22 Years of Life Milestone|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1purAy2MsOc|date=May 14, 2018|accessdate=January 25, 2020|author=TheOdd1sOut|via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Happy Birthday (To Me)|url=https://theodd1sout.com/blogs/comics/happy-birthday-to-me|website=theodd1sout.com|date=May 14, 2015|accessdate=January 25, 2020|author=Rallison, James}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Chandler Bing|Chandler]], Arizona, U.S.<ref name=\"Places of residence\">{{cite web|url= https://kasw.ewscloud.com/positivelyarizona/chandler-native-finds-success-as-theodd1sout-on-youtube/|title=Chandler Native Finds Success as \u2018TheOdd1sOut\u2019 on YouTube|publisher=www.yourphx.com|date=October 28, 2016 |accessdate=November 10, 2019|last=Waltz |first=Adam}}</ref>\n| nationality = American\n| residence = [[Glendale, California]], U.S.<ref name=\"Places of residence\" />\n| occupation={{flatlist|\n* [[YouTuber]]\n* artist\n* [[cartoonist]]\n* author\n}}\n| website = {{URL|theodd1sout.com}}\n| years_active = 2014\u2013present\n| channels = {{flatlist|\n*[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCo8bcnLyZH8tBIH9V1mLgqQ TheOdd1sOut]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC0GLNhtTu7yI8rl6ZZGeezw TheOdd2sOut]\n}}\n| subscribers = {{plainlist|\n* 14.1 million (''TheOdd1sOut'')\n* 2.4 million (''TheOdd2sOut'')\n}}\n| views = {{plainlist|\n* 2.82 billion (''TheOdd1sOut'')\n* 118.90 million (''TheOdd2sOut'')\n}}\n| network = None\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* [[Alex Clark (animator)|itsAlexClark]]\n* [[David Brown (British musician)|Boyinaband]]\n* Jaiden Animations\n* [[Jordan Maron]]\n* [[MrBeast]]\n* [[Anthony Padilla]]\n* SimpleFlips<ref>{{cite web|title=Tetris VS TheOdd1sOut|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eRxSw24NFQs|date=May 20, 2018|accessdate=December 14, 2019|author=SimpleFlips|via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n}}\n| catchphrase(s) = \"Thanks for watching, and wear your seat belt!\"\n| silver_button = yes\n| silver_year = 2016 (''TheOdd1sOut'')<br />2017 (''TheOdd2sOut'')\n| gold_button = yes\n| gold_year = 2016 (''TheOdd1sOut'')<br />2018 (''TheOdd2sOut'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/channel/UCo8bcnLyZH8tBIH9V1mLgqQ/futureprojections/subscribers|title=TheOdd1sOut Future Projections & Statistics |website=[[Social Blade]] |access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref>\n| diamond_button = yes\n| diamond_year = 2019 (''TheOdd1sOut'')\n| stats_update = December 6, 2019\n}}\n'''Robert James Rallison'''<ref name=\"Places of residence\"/><ref name=\"bmi\">{{cite web |title=Life Is Fun - BMI Repertoire Search |url=https://repertoire.bmi.com/DetailView.aspx?detail=titleid&keyid=41380359&ShowNbr=0&ShowSeqNbr=0&blnWriter=True&blnPublisher=True&blnArtist=True |website=BMI Repertoire |publisher=[[Broadcast Music, Inc.]] |accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/@davon.walters812/jaiden-animations-and-the-odd-1s-out-77d8b8e5312d|title=Jaiden Animations and the Odd 1\u2019s out|last=W|first=Davon|date=2017-12-18|website=Medium|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> (born May 14, 1996), known online as '''TheOdd1sOut''' (also spelled '''The Odd 1s Out''' or simply '''Odd1sOut'''), is an American [[YouTuber]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepearlpost.com/14375/entertainment/youtuber-of-the-month-james-rallison/|title=YouTuber of the month: James Rallison|work=The Pearl Post|publisher=[[Daniel Pearl Magnet High School]]|date=October 28, 2016 |accessdate=November 1, 2018|author=Bullock, Rachel}}</ref> As of March 2020, his primary [[YouTube]] channel had 14.1 million subscribers. His secondary YouTube channel ('''TheOdd2sOut''') had over 2.4&nbsp;million subscribers.\n\n== Early life ==\n[[File:Anthony Padilla and TheOdd1sOut 2019.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Rallison (right) in March 2019 with [[Anthony Padilla]]]]\n\nRallison was born in [[Chandler Bing|Chandler]], [[Arizona]], [[United States]].<ref name=\"Places of residence\" />\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Webcomics ===\nRallison uploaded the first strip of his webcomic ''TheOdd1sOut'' on June 14, 2012, on [[Tumblr]]<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news |url=https://crixeo.com/theodd1sout-comics/ |title=James Rallison on TheOdd1sOut Comics, Animations & New Book |date=June 11, 2018 |work=Crixeo |access-date=November 1, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707020123/https://crixeo.com/theodd1sout-comics/ |archive-date=July 7, 2018}}</ref> and later on iFunny.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ifunny.co/theodd1sout|title=TheOdd1sOut on iFunny|last=FunCorp|website=iFunny|access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== YouTube career ===\nOn August 30, 2014, Rallison started his YouTube channel as ''theodd1sout comic''. He started publishing animated videos in which he talks about his life story, his thoughts and opinions. By April 2016, his channel had gained over 278,000 subscribers, giving him a total of over 400,000 subscribers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tubefilter.com/2016/05/20/top-100-most-subscribed-youtube-channels-worldwide-april-2016/|title=Top 100 Most Subscribed YouTube Channels Worldwide \u2022 April 2016|date=May 20, 2016|work=[[Tubefilter]]|accessdate=April 28, 2017|author=Cohen, Joshua}}</ref>\n\nHis videos about working at [[Subway (restaurant)|Subway]], which he comedically refers to as \"Sooubway\",<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.foodbeast.com/news/sooubway-customers/|title=A Former 'Subway' Worker Recreates His WORST Customer Experiences in One Hilarious Animation|access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref> have been featured on [[Foodbeast]]. The website's writer, Peter Pham, described Rallison's videos as \"amazing\" and \"hilarious\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foodbeast.com/news/subway-animated/|title=Sooubway Worker Created An Animated Video Detailing His Experience There And It's Amazing|date=March 31, 2016|work=[[Foodbeast]]|accessdate=November 1, 2018|author=Pham, Peter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foodbeast.com/news/sooubway-episode-3/|title=A Former 'Subway' Worker Explains Why You Should Be Nice To Fast Food Employees in a Hilarious Animated Video|date=January 13, 2017|work=Foodbeast|accessdate=November 1, 2018|author=Pham, Peter}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Dave Trumbore of ''[[Collider (website)|Collider]]'' named Rallison one of five YouTubers who were \"poised for mainstream success\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/youtube-animators/|title=5 Indie YouTube Animators Poised for Mainstream Success|last=Trumbore|first=Dave|date=July 20, 2017|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref> In 2018, Kristin Brantley of Culturess reviewed his channel and webcomics favorably, writing, \"You\u2019ll be glued to the screen watching all of these hilarious clips and reading all his great comics.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://culturess.com/2018/08/18/10-hilarious-web-comic-artists-you-should-check-out-asap/ |last=Brantley|first=Kristin|title=10 hilarious webcomic artists you should check out ASAP |date=August 18, 2018 |website=Culturess  |access-date=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 2, 2017, Rallison created a second channel, TheOdd2sOut, in which he uploads extra content not involving animation. On April 3, 2018, TheOdd2sOut reached 1 million subscribers.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/channel/UC0GLNhtTu7yI8rl6ZZGeezw/realtime|title=TheOdd2sOut's Real-Time Subscriber Count \u2013 Social Blade YouTube Stats \u2013 YouTube Statistics|website=socialblade.com}}</ref>\n\nOn July 19, 2018, Rallison uploaded his first song called \"Life is Fun\", featuring [[David Brown (British musician)|Boyinaband]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CAb_bCtKuXg|title=Life is Fun \u2013 Ft. Boyinaband (Official Music Video)|via=YouTube|access-date=March 23, 2019}}</ref> It received almost 95&nbsp;million views.\n\nIn 2018, he was nominated on [[8th Streamy Awards]] in Animated category.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Haring |first1=Bruce |title=Streamy Awards Honor 24 Winners in Prelims To 8th Annual Event |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/streamy-awards-honor-24-winners-in-prelims-to-8th-annual-event-1202486685/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=October 21, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Schaffstall |first1=Katherine |title=Streamy Awards 2018: Winners List |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/streamy-awards-2018-winners-list-1146664 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=October 22, 2018  |date=October 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHis animated character appeared in the credits scene of ''[[YouTube Rewind]]: The Shape of 2017'' and in the universally panned ''[[YouTube Rewind 2018: Everyone Controls Rewind]]'' where he has a speaking role.<ref>{{Citation|last=YouTube Spotlight|title=YouTube Rewind 2018: Everyone Controls Rewind {{!}} #YouTubeRewind|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YbJOTdZBX1g|access-date=January 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn January 24, 2019, Rallison's main channel reached 10 million subscribers.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn March 12, 2019, Rallison was in [[MrBeast]]'s $200,000 YouTuber Battle Royale video. He was on a team with Jaiden Animations and [[Smosh|Anthony Padilla]] and they won the first round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/03/12/mrbeast-unleashes-hell-on-caspar-lee-anthony-padilla-and-jaidenanimations-in-youtuber-battle-royale-8893154/|title=MrBeast unleashes hell on Caspar Lee, Anthony Padilla and JaidenAnimations in YouTuber Battle Royale|publisher=Metro|date=March 12, 2019|accessdate=June 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn October 28, 2019, Rallison gave the earnings he made from the YouTuber Battle Royale to [[Team Trees|#TeamTrees]], a non-profit started by [[MrBeast]] that aims to plant 20 million trees by the end of 2019.<ref name=\"teamtrees\">{{cite news |last1=Griffin |first1=Louise |title=PewDiePie donates $69,420 to MrBeast\u2019s TeamTrees as he brands himself \u2018boomer\u2019 |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/10/31/pewdiepie-donates-69420-mrbeasts-teamtrees-brands-boomer-11019297/ |accessdate=November 6, 2019 |work=Metro |date=October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Other work ===\nRallison wrote a book titled ''The Odd 1s Out: How to Be Cool and Other Things I Definitely Learned from Growing Up'', which was released on July 31, 2018.<ref name=\"auto\" /> It was ranked No. 12 in the \"trade paperback\" category on ''[[Publishers Weekly]]''{{'}}s August 13, 2018 bestseller list.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/bookselling/article/77731-this-week-s-bestsellers-august-13-2018.html |title=This Week's Bestsellers: August 13, 2018 |last=Juris |first=Carolyn |date=August 10, 2018 |website=[[Publishers Weekly]] |access-date=January 9, 2019}}</ref> Rallison also worked on the board/card game ''Can't Catch Harry''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4bPezggGBa8|title=A Book I Made as an Adult - Youtube|last=|first=|date=|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=February 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Books ==\n*''TheOdd1sOut: How to Be Cool and Other Things I Definitely Learned from Growing Up'' (July 2018)\n*''TheOdd1sOut: The First Sequel'' (March 2020)\n\n== Discography ==\n* \"Life is Fun\" (featuring [[David Brown (British musician)|Boyinaband]]) (2018)\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Animation ===\n* 2017: ''[[YouTube Rewind]]: The Shape of 2017''\n* 2018: ''[[YouTube Rewind 2018: Everyone Controls Rewind]]''\n\n=== Voice acting ===\n* 2018: ''[[How It Should Have Ended]]'' as Martha (138th episode)\n* 2018: asdfmovie11 as Judge and Doctor of Psychology\n* 2018: ''[[YouTube Rewind 2018: Everyone Controls Rewind]]'' as himself\n* 2019: ''[[Meta Runner]]'' as Male Civilian\n* 2019: ''Meta Runner'' Special as Himself<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KMAsJBJFjzs|title=Fast Food Fight (Ft. TheOdd1sOut & Arin Hanson) - Meta Runner Special|date=October 19, 2019|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=October 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|James Rallison}}\n* {{YouTube|c=UCo8bcnLyZH8tBIH9V1mLgqQ}}\n{{Authority control|VIAF=4151776743918011202 |LCCN=n2018006007}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Odds1sOut, The}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American webcomic creators]]\n[[Category:Animators from Arizona]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2014]]\n[[Category:YouTube Diamond Play Button recipients]]\n[[Category:YouTube Gold Play Button recipients]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American YouTuber}}{{BLP sources|date=November 2019}}{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name= TheOdd1sOut \n| image = James_Rallison_at_Vidcon.jpg\n| caption = Rallison at [[VidCon]] 2017, wearing a shirt featuring his YouTube persona\n| birth_name = Robert James Rallison\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|5|14}}<ref>{{cite web|title=22 Years of Life Milestone|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1purAy2MsOc|date=May 14, 2018|accessdate=January 25, 2020|author=TheOdd1sOut|via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Happy Birthday (To Me)|url=https://theodd1sout.com/blogs/comics/happy-birthday-to-me|website=theodd1sout.com|date=May 14, 2015|accessdate=January 25, 2020|author=Rallison, James}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Chandler, Arizona]], U.S.<ref name=\"Places of residence\">{{cite web|url= https://kasw.ewscloud.com/positivelyarizona/chandler-native-finds-success-as-theodd1sout-on-youtube/|title=Chandler Native Finds Success as \u2018TheOdd1sOut\u2019 on YouTube|publisher=www.yourphx.com|date=October 28, 2016 |accessdate=November 10, 2019|last=Waltz |first=Adam}}</ref>\n| nationality = American\n| residence = [[Glendale, California]], U.S.<ref name=\"Places of residence\" />\n| occupation={{flatlist|\n* [[YouTuber]]\n* artist\n* [[cartoonist]]\n* author\n}}\n| website = {{URL|theodd1sout.com}}\n| years_active = 2014\u2013present\n| channels = {{flatlist|\n*[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCo8bcnLyZH8tBIH9V1mLgqQ TheOdd1sOut]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC0GLNhtTu7yI8rl6ZZGeezw TheOdd2sOut]\n}}\n| subscribers = {{plainlist|\n* 14.1 million (''TheOdd1sOut'')\n* 2.4 million (''TheOdd2sOut'')\n}}\n| views = {{plainlist|\n* 2.82 billion (''TheOdd1sOut'')\n* 118.90 million (''TheOdd2sOut'')\n}}\n| network = None\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* [[Alex Clark (animator)|itsAlexClark]]\n* [[David Brown (British musician)|Boyinaband]]\n* Jaiden Animations\n* [[Jordan Maron]]\n* [[MrBeast]]\n* [[Anthony Padilla]]\n* SimpleFlips<ref>{{cite web|title=Tetris VS TheOdd1sOut|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eRxSw24NFQs|date=May 20, 2018|accessdate=December 14, 2019|author=SimpleFlips|via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n}}\n| catchphrase(s) = \"Thanks for watching, and wear your seat belt!\"\n| silver_button = yes\n| silver_year = 2016 (''TheOdd1sOut'')<br />2017 (''TheOdd2sOut'')\n| gold_button = yes\n| gold_year = 2016 (''TheOdd1sOut'')<br />2018 (''TheOdd2sOut'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/channel/UCo8bcnLyZH8tBIH9V1mLgqQ/futureprojections/subscribers|title=TheOdd1sOut Future Projections & Statistics |website=[[Social Blade]] |access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref>\n| diamond_button = yes\n| diamond_year = 2019 (''TheOdd1sOut'')\n| stats_update = December 6, 2019\n}}\n'''Robert James Rallison'''<ref name=\"Places of residence\"/><ref name=\"bmi\">{{cite web |title=Life Is Fun - BMI Repertoire Search |url=https://repertoire.bmi.com/DetailView.aspx?detail=titleid&keyid=41380359&ShowNbr=0&ShowSeqNbr=0&blnWriter=True&blnPublisher=True&blnArtist=True |website=BMI Repertoire |publisher=[[Broadcast Music, Inc.]] |accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/@davon.walters812/jaiden-animations-and-the-odd-1s-out-77d8b8e5312d|title=Jaiden Animations and the Odd 1\u2019s out|last=W|first=Davon|date=2017-12-18|website=Medium|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> (born May 14, 1996), known online as '''TheOdd1sOut''' (also spelled '''The Odd 1s Out''' or simply '''Odd1sOut'''), is an American [[YouTuber]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepearlpost.com/14375/entertainment/youtuber-of-the-month-james-rallison/|title=YouTuber of the month: James Rallison|work=The Pearl Post|publisher=[[Daniel Pearl Magnet High School]]|date=October 28, 2016 |accessdate=November 1, 2018|author=Bullock, Rachel}}</ref> As of March 2020, his primary [[YouTube]] channel had 14.1 million subscribers. His secondary YouTube channel ('''TheOdd2sOut''') had over 2.4&nbsp;million subscribers.\n\n== Early life ==\n[[File:Anthony Padilla and TheOdd1sOut 2019.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Rallison (right) in March 2019 with [[Anthony Padilla]]]]\n\nRallison was born in [[Chandler, Arizona|Chandler]], [[Arizona]], [[United States]].<ref name=\"Places of residence\" />\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Webcomics ===\nRallison uploaded the first strip of his webcomic ''TheOdd1sOut'' on June 14, 2012, on [[Tumblr]]<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news |url=https://crixeo.com/theodd1sout-comics/ |title=James Rallison on TheOdd1sOut Comics, Animations & New Book |date=June 11, 2018 |work=Crixeo |access-date=November 1, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707020123/https://crixeo.com/theodd1sout-comics/ |archive-date=July 7, 2018}}</ref> and later on iFunny.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ifunny.co/theodd1sout|title=TheOdd1sOut on iFunny|last=FunCorp|website=iFunny|access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== YouTube career ===\nOn August 30, 2014, Rallison started his YouTube channel as ''theodd1sout comic''. He started publishing animated videos in which he talks about his life story, his thoughts and opinions. By April 2016, his channel had gained over 278,000 subscribers, giving him a total of over 400,000 subscribers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tubefilter.com/2016/05/20/top-100-most-subscribed-youtube-channels-worldwide-april-2016/|title=Top 100 Most Subscribed YouTube Channels Worldwide \u2022 April 2016|date=May 20, 2016|work=[[Tubefilter]]|accessdate=April 28, 2017|author=Cohen, Joshua}}</ref>\n\nHis videos about working at [[Subway (restaurant)|Subway]], which he comedically refers to as \"Sooubway\",<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.foodbeast.com/news/sooubway-customers/|title=A Former 'Subway' Worker Recreates His WORST Customer Experiences in One Hilarious Animation|access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref> have been featured on [[Foodbeast]]. The website's writer, Peter Pham, described Rallison's videos as \"amazing\" and \"hilarious\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foodbeast.com/news/subway-animated/|title=Sooubway Worker Created An Animated Video Detailing His Experience There And It's Amazing|date=March 31, 2016|work=[[Foodbeast]]|accessdate=November 1, 2018|author=Pham, Peter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foodbeast.com/news/sooubway-episode-3/|title=A Former 'Subway' Worker Explains Why You Should Be Nice To Fast Food Employees in a Hilarious Animated Video|date=January 13, 2017|work=Foodbeast|accessdate=November 1, 2018|author=Pham, Peter}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Dave Trumbore of ''[[Collider (website)|Collider]]'' named Rallison one of five YouTubers who were \"poised for mainstream success\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/youtube-animators/|title=5 Indie YouTube Animators Poised for Mainstream Success|last=Trumbore|first=Dave|date=July 20, 2017|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref> In 2018, Kristin Brantley of Culturess reviewed his channel and webcomics favorably, writing, \"You\u2019ll be glued to the screen watching all of these hilarious clips and reading all his great comics.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://culturess.com/2018/08/18/10-hilarious-web-comic-artists-you-should-check-out-asap/ |last=Brantley|first=Kristin|title=10 hilarious webcomic artists you should check out ASAP |date=August 18, 2018 |website=Culturess  |access-date=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 2, 2017, Rallison created a second channel, TheOdd2sOut, in which he uploads extra content not involving animation. On April 3, 2018, TheOdd2sOut reached 1 million subscribers.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/channel/UC0GLNhtTu7yI8rl6ZZGeezw/realtime|title=TheOdd2sOut's Real-Time Subscriber Count \u2013 Social Blade YouTube Stats \u2013 YouTube Statistics|website=socialblade.com}}</ref>\n\nOn July 19, 2018, Rallison uploaded his first song called \"Life is Fun\", featuring [[David Brown (British musician)|Boyinaband]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CAb_bCtKuXg|title=Life is Fun \u2013 Ft. Boyinaband (Official Music Video)|via=YouTube|access-date=March 23, 2019}}</ref> It received almost 95&nbsp;million views.\n\nIn 2018, he was nominated on [[8th Streamy Awards]] in Animated category.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Haring |first1=Bruce |title=Streamy Awards Honor 24 Winners in Prelims To 8th Annual Event |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/streamy-awards-honor-24-winners-in-prelims-to-8th-annual-event-1202486685/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=October 21, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Schaffstall |first1=Katherine |title=Streamy Awards 2018: Winners List |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/streamy-awards-2018-winners-list-1146664 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=October 22, 2018  |date=October 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHis animated character appeared in the credits scene of ''[[YouTube Rewind]]: The Shape of 2017'' and in the universally panned ''[[YouTube Rewind 2018: Everyone Controls Rewind]]'' where he has a speaking role.<ref>{{Citation|last=YouTube Spotlight|title=YouTube Rewind 2018: Everyone Controls Rewind {{!}} #YouTubeRewind|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YbJOTdZBX1g|access-date=January 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn January 24, 2019, Rallison's main channel reached 10 million subscribers.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn March 12, 2019, Rallison was in [[MrBeast]]'s $200,000 YouTuber Battle Royale video. He was on a team with Jaiden Animations and [[Smosh|Anthony Padilla]] and they won the first round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/03/12/mrbeast-unleashes-hell-on-caspar-lee-anthony-padilla-and-jaidenanimations-in-youtuber-battle-royale-8893154/|title=MrBeast unleashes hell on Caspar Lee, Anthony Padilla and JaidenAnimations in YouTuber Battle Royale|publisher=Metro|date=March 12, 2019|accessdate=June 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn October 28, 2019, Rallison gave the earnings he made from the YouTuber Battle Royale to [[Team Trees|#TeamTrees]], a non-profit started by [[MrBeast]] that aims to plant 20 million trees by the end of 2019.<ref name=\"teamtrees\">{{cite news |last1=Griffin |first1=Louise |title=PewDiePie donates $69,420 to MrBeast\u2019s TeamTrees as he brands himself \u2018boomer\u2019 |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/10/31/pewdiepie-donates-69420-mrbeasts-teamtrees-brands-boomer-11019297/ |accessdate=November 6, 2019 |work=Metro |date=October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Other work ===\nRallison wrote a book titled ''The Odd 1s Out: How to Be Cool and Other Things I Definitely Learned from Growing Up'', which was released on July 31, 2018.<ref name=\"auto\" /> It was ranked No. 12 in the \"trade paperback\" category on ''[[Publishers Weekly]]''{{'}}s August 13, 2018 bestseller list.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/bookselling/article/77731-this-week-s-bestsellers-august-13-2018.html |title=This Week's Bestsellers: August 13, 2018 |last=Juris |first=Carolyn |date=August 10, 2018 |website=[[Publishers Weekly]] |access-date=January 9, 2019}}</ref> Rallison also worked on the board/card game ''Can't Catch Harry''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4bPezggGBa8|title=A Book I Made as an Adult - Youtube|last=|first=|date=|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=February 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Books ==\n*''TheOdd1sOut: How to Be Cool and Other Things I Definitely Learned from Growing Up'' (July 2018)\n*''TheOdd1sOut: The First Sequel'' (March 2020)\n\n== Discography ==\n* \"Life is Fun\" (featuring [[David Brown (British musician)|Boyinaband]]) (2018)\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Animation ===\n* 2017: ''[[YouTube Rewind]]: The Shape of 2017''\n* 2018: ''[[YouTube Rewind 2018: Everyone Controls Rewind]]''\n\n=== Voice acting ===\n* 2018: ''[[How It Should Have Ended]]'' as Martha (138th episode)\n* 2018: asdfmovie11 as Judge and Doctor of Psychology\n* 2018: ''[[YouTube Rewind 2018: Everyone Controls Rewind]]'' as himself\n* 2019: ''[[Meta Runner]]'' as Male Civilian\n* 2019: ''Meta Runner'' Special as Himself<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KMAsJBJFjzs|title=Fast Food Fight (Ft. TheOdd1sOut & Arin Hanson) - Meta Runner Special|date=October 19, 2019|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=October 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|James Rallison}}\n* {{YouTube|c=UCo8bcnLyZH8tBIH9V1mLgqQ}}\n{{Authority control|VIAF=4151776743918011202 |LCCN=n2018006007}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Odds1sOut, The}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American webcomic creators]]\n[[Category:Animators from Arizona]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2014]]\n[[Category:YouTube Diamond Play Button recipients]]\n[[Category:YouTube Gold Play Button recipients]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n", "name_user": "Mrspagehttiwe2019", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(APRIL FOOLS\